From: mt7921u Forensic Audit Project <mt7921u@project.local>
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: mt7921: complete TWT implementation phases 2-3

Implement TWT Phase 2 (station capability + debugfs) and Phase 3
(eBPF hook stub) for the mt7921 driver.

Phase 2a: Add IEEE80211_HE_MAC_CAP0_TWT_REQ and TWT_RES capability
bits for NL80211_IFTYPE_STATION in mt7921_init_he_caps(), enabling
the device to act as both TWT requester and responder in station mode.

Phase 2b: Add twt_debugfs.c providing /sys/kernel/debug/ieee80211/phyX/
mt76/twt_stats for visibility into active TWT agreements and service
period counters. Iterates device wcid table to display per-flow
parameters (wcid, table_id, flow_id, mantissa, exp, duration, tsf,
protection, flowtype, trigger).

Phase 2c: Add struct mt7921_twt_agrt_stats for tracking agreement
count and missed service period events (stub until firmware event
support).

Phase 2d: Wire mt7921_twt_debugfs_init() into mt7921_init_debugfs()
and store debugfs_dir in mt792x_dev for later access.

Phase 3: Add eBPF TWT hook stub documentation block describing the
intended BPF_PROG_TYPE_WIFI_TWT interface for filtering, monitoring,
and dynamic adjustment of TWT agreements.

Bus-aware: no PCIe/SDIO-specific code paths affected. All new code
is shared across bus types.

Signed-off-by: mt7921u Forensic Audit Project <mt7921u@project.local>
---

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/Makefile b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/Makefile
